-- Ecuador President Correa Claims Victory in Today’s Election
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2013-02-17T22:41:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-17/ecuador-president-correa-claims-victory-in-today-s-election.html
 Ecuadorean President Rafael Correa
claimed victory in today’s national elections, defeating seven
opposition candidates for another four-year term.   “This victory belongs to each of you,” Correa said today
from the presidential palace in Quito. “No one and nothing is
stopping this revolution friends, we are making history.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
